== List of Sacred Sites == {| class="wikitable" ! No. !! Regional No. !! Shrine/Temple !! Location !! Remarks |- style="background-color:#ddf" ! | colspan="4" | '''Ise: Path of Shinto-Buddhist Unity''' |- ! | Special || {{ill|Kōtai Jingū|ja|皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} || [[:en:Ise, Mie|Ise City]] || [[:en:Twenty-Two Shrines|Twenty-Two Shrines]] |- ! | Special || {{ill|Toyouke Daijingu|ja|豊受大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke Daijingu|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} || [[:en:Ise, Mie|Ise City]] || [[:en:Twenty-Two Shrines|Twenty-Two Shrines]] |- style="background-color:#ddf" ! | colspan="4" | '''Wakayama: Path of Purity''' |- !1 | Wakayama 1 || [[:en:Kumano Hayatama Taisha|Kumano Hayatama Taisha]] || [[:en:Shingū, Wakayama|Shingū City]] || |- !2 | Wakayama 2 || [[:en:Seiganto-ji|Seiganto-ji]] || [[:en:Nachikatsuura|Nachikatsuura, Higashimuro]] || [[:en:Saigoku Kannon Pilgrimage|Saigoku Kannon Pilgrimage]] |- [... continued for all listed shrines and temples in similar fashion ...] |- !150 | Shiga 18 || [[:en:Enryaku-ji|Enryaku-ji]] || [[:en:Ōtsu|Ōtsu City]] || Headquarters of [[:en:Tiantai|Tendai]], {{ill|New Saigoku 33 Kannon|ja|新西国三十三箇所|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Saigoku 33 Kannon|qq=}} |}
== Goshuinchō (Pilgrimage Stamp Book) == An official {{ill|Goshuinchō|ja|朱印帳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Goshuinchō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 朱印 (神社仏閣)}} is available for 2,700 yen (as of Reiwa 5 [2023]).<ref>[http://shinbutsureijou.net/shuincho.html Pilgrimage Stamp Book - Shinbutsu Reijō Association]</ref> However, some shrines and temples do not distribute it. It is also not available at the starting point, Ise Grand Shrine. Previously, it was distributed at the Jingū Kaikan near Naikū, but currently, it is no longer available. Since September 8, Heisei 30 (2018), two new shrines and temples were added, making the old Goshuinchō insufficient. As a relief measure, paper stamps are available at these newly joined locations. The current Goshuinchō has the names of shrines and temples pre-printed.
